Rhabdomyosarcoma (RMS) is the most common soft tissue sarcoma in 
childhood. It accounts for 6% of all childhood malignancies (commonly 
aged <10yrs). The majority of cases are sporadic. Most are either embryonal or alveolar (more aggressive) subtypes. Botryoid (good prognosis) and 
spindle cell types are also recognized. A small number of cases are associated with Li–Fraumeni syndrome.
